Rolf Harris’s daughter sent him an email asking what she would inherit and comparing his £11million fortune to ‘winning the lottery’, his trial heard.

The e-mail was shown to jurors at Southwark Crown Court after Bindi Nicholls took the stand to defend her father, insisting he did not indecently assault an underage girl.

But she said the message, which was released by the judge today after being shown to jurors last week, was being taken out of context - and denied 'helping' her 84-year-old father for any other reason than to tell the truth.

