‘It is like being 
told that you will be winning the lottery at some point so you get 
excited and dream about the things that you could do which is quite 
normal, everyone would dream about that.’

In the email Mrs Nicholls and her husband Craig described Harris's fortune as being in the region of £11million.

The email referred to her relationship with Harris' 90-year-old brother Bruce, saying: 'This is important stuff!

'When
 you are gone we are all left with the aftermath of people fighting over
 stuff, I'm left with Bruce and Elaine (and you know how they feel about
 me!) and I'm alone with it all.

'Do you want to write letters to 
people you care about... do you want to give people things before you 
go? How do you want to be remembered?

'Please, you don't want people being left confused, angry, upset and fraught with sadness and grief.'

The e-mail was presented to the jury 
